    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_495932">Pirating the game solves nothing, and it frustrates me that people think this is an answer.  Don't buy the game, don't pirate the game, don't give any title using this type of DRM the time of day.  If you have a 'heroin-class addiction' to Assassin's Creed 2 then rent the console version or buy the game used.  There are plenty of other publishers out there who want your money and won't ask their customers to jump through these hoops in an attempt to prevent pirates from playing their games as well.<br />
<br />
It seems there is only one thing that Ubisoft is more afraid of than pirates, and that's apathy.  The fear that they spend millions on publishing a game only to watch everyone shrug their shoulders, give a 'meh...' and turn their back on the baby they've spent millions on hyping and creating anticipation for in hopes of making barrels full of money.  I'm personally shrugging my shoulders and turning my back on Ubisoft.<br />
<br />
Edit:  When I mentioned &quot;rent the console version or buy the game used&quot; I should clarify that I meant buy the console version used, as this DRM prevents you from re-selling your PC version.</div>
