    <div align="left" id="post_message_495939">While I won't put words in Toprem's mouth, by buying the game you are accepting Ubisoft's DRM as it is, regardless of whether you pirate the game in order to play it.  You are telling Ubisoft that the DRM is acceptable to you because you're giving them your money for their DRM-laden product.<br />
<br />
Whether you install the packaged product you bought, keep it on a shelf and download a pirated version, or throw the unopened box into a woodchipper and never play the game, the act of giving them your money tells them you support their actions.</div>
