    <div align="left" id="post_message_495955">Wow, very glad Ubisoft doesn't publish anything I'm interested in playing. I mean no offline mode at all? Geez. Suddenly I'm relieved the only franchise from Ubisoft I've been interested in has been abandoned.<br />
<br />
If there were some benefits to staying connected, some bonuses you would not otherwise get, but you could still play the base game offline... then I could see it not being as big a deal. But locking people out of the game completely, and not letting them play offline - yeah, there's absolutely no way that can end poorly. If gaming companies were more competent then I might have more faith, but I can't even register a 3 year old game made by one of the better developer houses because their sites loop back on themselves and they've updated their sites out of the ability to register their games for free DLCs... and that's so far from being the only issue I've had with just a slightly older game when it came to basic stuff, just the latest issue.<br />
<br />
CAD has a strip about Ubi's system too: <a href="http://www.cad-comic.com/cad/20100219" target="_blank">http://www.cad-comic.com/cad/20100219</a></div>
