    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_495974">All DRM has managed to do is piss off (paying)customers.  It doesn't stop pirates, even with the millions they pour into it each year. Cracked games still show up online with in a week, or weeks before the game is even released.<br />
<br />
I think most people that pirate games would like to pay for and support companies that make good games, no DRM and reasonable prices or deals (like you find on steam often) are good ways.</div>
