</div>This. The people/teams that actually pirate stuff WILL get it cracked, most probably view it as a challenge and want to get it cracked. The only game Ive ever seen take any length of time to get cracked after it was released was BioShock 1, it took it like a week to get cracked and its why I, regretfully, bought it. BioShock 2 was cracked by the day it was released, if not earlier.<br />
<br />
The only way to make something truly hard to crack is to make something like the PS3, which has only been partially cracked and afaik still can't play copied PS3 games. Piracy is fairly big on the other consoles, not as big as PC pirating, but for developers to only target PC gamers with this ******** is just that, ********.<br />
