</div>Shame you are going off what you read then. As you are missing out on one of the best Rogue/Assassin single player games to come out in many many years.<br />
<br />
As for Bagheera's comments on DRM being a good thing, sorry man you have missed the boat. DRM does not deter pirates or even slow them down, even on the most expensive software. The only thing it does is punish the paying customer. That said, it still does not justify stealing it. Run a pirated copy to avoid the DRM crap if you purchased it as well? Sure. Download a pirated copy to &quot;Try before you buy&quot; if there is no decent Demo? Sure. Download a pirated copy and justify it by with some weak argument about not supporting the company? No. If you don't want to support the company, then don't use Any of their software Period. Sorry but theft is theft, be it a loaf of bread, a car or a piece of software. There is no grey middle ground here no matter how you try and justify it.</div>
