</div>It's a valuable commodity.  Obviously.  I mean, you want to play it, right?  You just don't want to play it enough to pay for it, but you still want to play it enough to play it for free, despite the illegality of it.  You can't have it both ways, claiming that it's worthless, but then saying that you have a desire and some sort of imagined right to play it.<br />
