    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_496005">DRM is totally unnecessary and this is beyond absurd.  Read articles by the guys who made GoG.com.  They are based in Poland and a decade ago the ONLY way to even get games in Poland was to buy pirated copies (no hi speed internet to download it obviously).  They successfully built a business selling games without DRM in a market where only pirates existed and nobody had any moral problems with it.  How?  By making a good quality product and more importantly making the experience of buying it and installing it so damned simple and convenient that people would pay the extra dollar to have the guarantee the quality.  <br />
<br />
The older I get the less and less willing I am to hand over 50 dollars to deal with **** like that.  I really wanted Spore until I heard about the DRM.  Haven't even downloaded a demo of it.<br />
<br />
Pirates shouldn't even be a part of this conversation.  They are nothing but a ***** man in this issue.  They won't buy the game no matter what.  Who cares how much money you don't make off of them.  You won't make a dime anyway.  Start rewarding people who pay for the game.  This simply punishes them.</div>
